# Per-service hex color configuration for docker compose log output.
#
# Used by integration_tests/demo/colorize_compose_logs.py to apply
# consistent, configurable 24-bit ANSI foreground colors to each
# service's log-line prefix.
#
# Format:  SERVICE_NAME=HEXCOLOR   (# comments and blank lines ignored)
#
# The service name matches the docker-compose service name
# (e.g. "finder", not "finder-1").  Replica suffixes (-1, -2, …) are
# stripped automatically, so a single entry covers all replicas.
#
# Override the config file path at runtime:
#   COMPOSE_SERVICE_COLORS=/path/to/alt.env ./run_multi_actor_integration_test.sh
#
# Colors are applied only when stdout is a TTY; plain-text output
# (redirected to a file or pipe) is left unmodified.

